data.clean_description: The garden , as it is commonly known in Andalusia and some areas of Spain , is one of the best types of commercial hash produced by Morocco. Also called hardala , jurdala or jardula. Normally it usually has these type of characteristics a bright black or yellow color , with a sticky and moldable texture Similar to that of a gum , intense smell of grass with touches of afgani. It can reach a more oily texture , on more than one occasion I have smoked it in the bubbler without problem , as if it were oil.
data.name: 2.5 g The best types of commercial hash produced
